# Import Strategy Documentation
# ==============================
#
# This file documents the import strategy used for this demo.
#
# IMPORTANT: We are using CLI imports instead of import blocks because
# the libvirt provider requires UUIDs for import operations, and import
# blocks cannot use dynamic UUID resolution (bash commands).
#
# Import blocks would look like this (but won't work with libvirt):
#   import {
#     to = libvirt_network.legacy
#     id = "legacy-network"  # ← This fails! Needs UUID, not name
#   }
#
# Instead, we use CLI imports with dynamic UUID resolution:
#   LEGACY_UUID=$(virsh net-uuid legacy-network)
#   terraform import libvirt_network.legacy "$LEGACY_UUID"
#
# This approach works because:
# 1. We can get UUIDs dynamically using virsh
# 2. CLI imports accept the UUID as a parameter
# 3. The import succeeds and resources are added to state
#
# Networks imported:
# - libvirt_network.legacy (legacy-network)
# - libvirt_network.app (app-network)
# - libvirt_network.db (db-network)
EOF

